            "title": "LVMH shares expected to fall after disappointing results",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>PARIS, Jan 28 (Reuters) - LVMH shares were seen down 3-4% on Wednesday after its fourth-quarter results, according to traders' pre-market indications, with the market disappointed at the luxury group's weaker margin and cautious tone on the first signs of demand recovery.</p><p>\n              The French group said domestic Chinese sales grew in the quarter, as the key market returns to growth, but analysts said the results were less encouraging than expected after peers Richemont and Burberry earlier this month.</p><!-- Article --><p>\n              LVMH CEO Bernard Arnault told a press conference on Tuesday that there was \"reason to be a little cautious\" given geopolitical crises and economic uncertainty.</p><p></p><p> (Reporting by Helen Reid, Editing by Louise Heavens)</p></div>",
